# Environment — never committed, never a Flutter asset
# Real per-flavor files follow flow's `.env.<flavor>` convention (`.env.dev`,
# `.env.production`); only the checked-in `.example` templates are tracked.
.env
.env.*
!.env.dev.example
!.env.production.example

